title: Fort Matanzas National Monument: Photos & Multimedia
body: Photos & Multimedia              1934 National Archive Footage   Loading the player...       Visit JWPlayer docs for keyboard shortcuts  Duration:3 minutes, 40 seconds  This footage was made in 1934 following the transfer of Fort Matanzas and other eastern sites to the National Park Service.               Osprey_21 Jan 2014   Loading the player...       Visit JWPlayer docs for keyboard shortcuts  Duration:2 minutes, 4 seconds  Constantly surveying its surroundings, an osprey finishes a mid-day meal at its favorite spot atop a dead oak tree along State Route A1A. With the Matanzas River on one side and the Atlantic Ocean on the other, osprey have no problem finding a meal whenever the mood strikes!           An osprey lands on a dead tree with a recent catch. NPS photo  Head over to the Nature & Science page to check out our slideshow of an osprey.        Rendering of Ft Matanzas   View a 3D rendering of a laser scan done by the University of South Florida! http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=N3PEdCJ-0tE      The Fort Matanzas Great Horned Owls in Living Color!!
